ontologyFramework.OFProcedureManagment

Interface OFProcedureInterface

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Algorithm

    public interface OFProcedureInterface
extends java.io.Serializable
    This interface represents a Procedure object. Instances of this interface will be create in accord from OFProcedureBuilder. An implementation of this Interface is Algorithm which uses Quartz engine.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Buoncomapgni Luca

        void initialise(org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual procedureInd,
              OWLReferences ontoRef,
              OFBuildedListInvoker listInvoker,
              java.lang.String[] keyWords)
        This method will be called just after all building times. It should be used to initialize variables that need to get data from the ontology.
        Parameters:
        procedureInd - ontological individual which is reflacting a procedure
        ontoRef - reference to an OWL ontology
        listInvoker - static list manager of builded entity
        keyWords - coming from the builder ontological definition througth data type: hasTypeKeyWor exactly 1 string

      • getEventName

        java.lang.String getEventName(OWLReferences ontoRef)
        Get the individual name of the Event attached to the ontological representation of a procedure. It should be able to update themselves without call a building mechanism.
        Parameters:
        ontoRef - reference to an OWL ontology
        Returns:
        the individual name of the Event attached to this procedure.

      • setEventResult

        void setEventResult(boolean result)
        The name returned by: getEventName(OWLReferences) will be used during checking (as an example: AlgorithmCheckerJob) time to retrieve their result through the Event list (OFBuildedListInvoker). When its boolean result is available this method is called to deal with a possible change of event result. So, it should use run() stop() or shotdown() to change the state of the procedure.
        Parameters:
        result - the boolean value associate to the Event which name is given by getEventName( OWLReferences)

      • getEventResult

        Returns:
        the boolean value associate to the Event which name is given by getEventName( OWLReferences)

      • setTimeTrigger

        void setTimeTrigger(java.lang.Object timeTrigger)

When its returnig variable is available this method is called to deal with a possible change of trigger. So, it should use run() stop() or shotdown() to change the state of the procedure.

      • getCheckerJob

        java.lang.Object getCheckerJob()
        Since a procedure is always linked to a Checker procedure, which has the objective to synchronize ontological changes of the procedure individual it is convenient to represent the relate Checker object inside this implementation giving an external access to it througth this method.
        Returns:
        the checker procedure (must be a runnable implementation)

      • getMainJob

        java.lang.Object getMainJob()
        It may be useful to describe a procedure in a way that its computational steps are in an separate runnable class. This allows more flexibility in scheduling and building phases. If this is the case than, this implementaion will define the shape of a generic algorithm. Than different Instances of this class will be related to particolar scripts pointed by the returning value of this method.
        Returns:
        the runnable implementation of this specific procedure.
